Class CowHerd

  • java.lang.Object
    • jmarkov.jmdp.MDP<S,A>
      • jmarkov.jmdp.FiniteMDP<S,A>

          • examples.jmdp.CowHerd

  • public class CowHerd
extends FiniteDP<examples.jmdp.CowQuantity,examples.jmdp.CowActions>
    The cow herd problem. Given the prices on a horizon decide whether keep or sell the cow herd. There is a max number of cows per period. If you keep the cows there will be about 1.5 times the current number of cows in the next period.
    Author:
    Germán Riaño
